---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const LAST_UPDATED = 'February 17, 2026';       // TODO: update when you change this page
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy Policy for EM Behavioral PrepKit — how we collect, use, and protect your data."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16">
    <div class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-white mb-3">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm">Last updated: {LAST_UPDATED}</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-dark space-y-8">

      <section>
        <h2>1. What This Site Is</h2>
        <p>
          EM Behavioral PrepKit is a free, open-source behavioral interview preparation guide for
          engineering managers and technical leaders. It is a static website with no user
          accounts, no login, and no server-side data processing.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Type</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Stored where</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Cookie consent preference</td>
              <td>Remember your privacy choice</td>
              <td>Your browser (localStorage)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Page views &amp; interactions</td>
              <td>Understand usage (analytics only)</td>
              <td>Analytics provider — only if you consent</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p>
          We do <strong>not</strong> collect names, email addresses, payment information, or
          any other personally identifiable information. No account is required to use this site.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. Cookies &amp; localStorage</h2>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Key</th><th>Category</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Expires</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>gdpr_consent</code></td>
              <td>Strictly Necessary</td>
              <td>Stores your cookie preference so we don't ask again</td>
              <td>Until you clear site data</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p>
          Analytics cookies are only set after you click <em>Accept All</em> or enable Analytics
          in <em>Cookie Preferences</em>. You can change your preference at any time via the
          "Cookie Preferences" link in the page footer.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. Analytics</h2>
        <p>
          If you consent to analytics cookies, we may use an analytics service to collect
          aggregate, anonymous usage data such as page views and click events. No personal
          profiles are built from this data, and it is not sold to third parties.
        </p>
        <p>
          Analytics are disabled by default and are only activated after your explicit consent.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Service</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Privacy Policy</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>GitHub Pages</td>
              <td>Website hosting</td>
              <td><a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" class="text-violet-400 hover:text-violet-300" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Privacy Statement</a></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Google Analytics</td>
              <td>Anonymous usage analytics (only if you consent)</td>
              <td><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" class="text-violet-400 hover:text-violet-300" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Privacy Policy</a></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>Under GDPR and similar regulations, you have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Access</strong> — request a copy of any data we hold about you</li>
          <li><strong>Erasure</strong> — request deletion of your data (clearing browser localStorage removes all stored data on our end)</li>
          <li><strong>Withdraw consent</strong> — change your cookie preferences at any time via the footer link</li>
          <li><strong>Complain</strong> — lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Because this is a static site with no server-side storage, clearing your browser's
          site data effectively removes all data associated with your visit.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          Your consent preference is stored locally in your browser until you clear your site
          data or change your preference. We retain no server-side records of individual visitors.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy occasionally. When we do, we will update the "Last updated"
          date at the top and, if the changes materially affect how we use your data, we will
          bump the consent version so you are asked to re-consent.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>9. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about this policy? Open an issue at{' '}
          <a href="https://github.com/chitamoor/interview-prep/issues" class="text-violet-400 hover:text-violet-300" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">github.com/chitamoor/interview-prep/issues</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
